<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-200-005 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 473 180</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  March 18 1991 v8 n11 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New SCSI adapters designed to meet users' demands. (Adaptec Inc,Distributed Processing Technology Corp and Future Domain Corp.)andO;(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sulivan, Kristina B.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Adaptec Inc. (Product introduction)Distributed Processing Technology Corp. (Product introduction)Future Domain Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    ADPT.andO;Product:   Adaptec AHA-1510 (Input-output board) (Product introduction)Distributed Processing Technology SmartCache Plus (Peripheralcontroller) (Product introduction)Disk Maestro TM Disk Management System (Add-in/on software)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     InterfaceSmall Computer Systems InterfaceProduct IntroductionPeripheral Controllers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>New SCSI Adapters Designed To Meet Users' DemandsandM;Adaptec Inc., Distributed Processing Technology and Future Domain Corp.andO;recently announced new Small Computer System Interface host adapters designedto fulfill a growing demand for the interface.andM;Adaptec this month announced and began shipping its AT-to-SCSI host adapterdesigned for non-disk applications.andP;  The AHA-1500 &quot;fills a need for'dedicated connectivity'--or non-disk peripherals that don't require a BIOS,&quot;said Paul Matteucci, director of marketing for the publicly held Milpitas,Calif., firm.andM;The AHA-1510 is available to peripherals makers for less than $60, he said,but does not include the floppy controller, jumpers and BIOS logic requiredon higher-priced SCSI disk controllers.andM;At the CeBIT '91 computer trade show last week in Hannover, Germany, DPTannounced and started shipping an AT-bus SCSI controller that can beconfigured with or without cache memory.andM;Called SmartCache Plus, the $595 product can be converted to a cachingcontroller by adding a $555 module that includes 512K bytes of memory,expandable to 16M bytes, said officials from the privately held Orlando,Fla., firm.andM;Future Domain last month upgraded its $70 Disk Maestro TM Disk ManagementSystem software.andP;  Version 6.0 adds support for more than 140 types of SCSIdrives, including rewritable optical and removable hard disks, as well as anylogical drive with up to 511M bytes in capacity in an extended DOS partition,according to company officials in Irvine, Calif.andP;  Users of version 5.2 mustpay the full $70 to upgrade.andM;Analysts confirmed the strong demand for SCSI controllers.andP;  &quot;The largestopportunity today for non-hard-disk SCSI adapters is in thequarter-inch-cartridge tape industry,&quot; said Tim Williams, president ofEnterprise Information systems Inc., a market-research firm in Issaquah,Wash.andP;  That is likely to change in the next five years, however, ashelical-scan tape, CD ROM optical, rewritable optical and scanner marketsbecome more popular and require SCSI, he said.andM;Adaptec can be reached at (408) 945-8600, DPT at (407) 830-5522, and FutureDomain at (714) 253-0400.andO;</TEXT></DOC>